Defendant in custody.
The defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total of eight (8) years.  That is three (3) years initial confinement followed by five (5) years extended supervision.
The Court finds the defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarcaration Program but is eligible for the Substance Abuse Program after the defendant served twelve (12) months of his sentence.
Conditions of extended supervision:
1) pay $1,200.00 fine plus costs, total of $2,527.00;
2) assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
3) maintain absolute sobriety;
4) defendant is not to operate a motor vehicle without ignition interlock for period of extended supervision;
5) defendant is not to enter liquor stores and/or taverns;
6) maintain fulltime work or work search;
7) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.
In addition, the Court orders a thirty-six (36) month DL revocation and period of ignition interlock.
Defendant has credit for 68 days.
$2000.00 cash bail is ordered applied to fine and costs.
Minutes.
